      description "Voltage at which BFU must disconnect main load. Main load is disconnected when value of systemVoltage is below mainLoadUndervoltageDisconnect. For example, default value -460 = -46.0 V means that main load is disconnected if systemVoltage is -45.9 V. During deprecation period, setting of mainLoadUndervoltageDisconnect is converted and mirrored to BatteryBackup.mainLoadDisconnectLevel.; range -480..-400; Default value: -460; Status info: Since 18A. Replaced by mainLoadDisconnectLevel on MO BatteryBackup. Planned to be removed..";
