      description "The offset for the disconnected voltage above which the Battery Fuse Unit (BFU) reconnects the load. Applies to both main and priority load. The main load is reconnected when system voltage is above (mainLoadUndervoltageDisconect - undervoltageDisconnectCeaseOffset). systemVoltage = batteryVoltage when the system is running on battery supply. Example: The default values gives a main load undervoltage reconnection at -460 – 70 = -530 (-53.0 V DC), the load is reconnected if systemVoltage is e.g. -53.1 V. Note: the batteries are reconnected when systemVoltage is above (mainLoadUndervoltageDisconnected -underVoltageDisconnectCeaseOffset) and batteryVoltage is above -39.0V. systemVoltage is an attribute in MO PowerSupply. batteryVoltage is an attribute in MO BatteryBackup.; range 10..100; Default value: 70; Status info: Since 18A. Planned to be removed..";
